The agent incorrectly included "targetAudience" as an argument in the TemplateRecommender_suggestTemplates function call, which is not part of the accepted parameters, causing a mismatch with the expected function signature.
The agent included an extraneous "beginner" option in the sessionOptions array, which was not expectedâ€”instead, only "45 minutes" should have been specified according to the required parameters.

The agent failed to invoke the required OnlineFitnessClass_register tool and instead asked the user for more information, missing the clear instruction to register for a beginner's yoga class. It did not make any tool call as expected.

The agent called the correct function but used "Technology" (capital T) in sectorList instead of the expected lowercase "technology," resulting in a mismatch with the evaluator's strict parameter case sensitivity.
